LC in RLIN, 3-29-94 (hdg.: Cronin, James W., 1931-)

Fermi remembered, 2004: CIP t.p. (James Cronin)

New York times WWW site, viewed Aug. 31, 2016 (in obituary published Aug. 30: James W. Cronin; b. James Watson Cronin, Sept. 29, 1931, Chicago; d. Thursday [Aug. 25, 2016], St. Paul, aged 84; physicist who shared a Nobel Prize for repudiating a fundamental principle of physics and explaining why the universe survived the Big Bang with anything in it)
